Yan-Bo: (Today's the day of the meeting with Law and Maeok...)
Sad Beast: Master Yan-Bo!
Sad Beast: I heard about the accident during the Edensnatch, but I haven't been able find you since. Today I've finally caught up to you!
Yan-Bo: The Edensnatch...
Sad Beast: Yes, Master. Are the rumors true?
Disappointed Beast: We wanna know just exactly what happened that day before we can feel at ease joining your school.
Yan-Bo: I'm sorry. It's a little complicated...
Sad Beast: We believe you, Master. But we want to hear it from your own mouth!
Yan-Bo: All I can say right now is that I did not cheat. The investigation isn't over yet, but in a few days the Capybara Chieftain will announce his findings...
Sad Beast: Master Yan-Bo, can't you tell your future disciples anything at all? How can I call you Master otherwise?
Yan-Bo: W-wait a moment!
Disappointed Beast: I told you so. Yan-Bo's not all you've cracked him up to be!
Sad Beast: I misjudged you, Yan-Bo!
Yan-Bo: This is even more serious than I thought... If I go looking for Law and Maeok now I'll only drag them into it too...
Yan-Bo: I'll return to the Tribe first and ask them to carry them a message instead...
Alliance Guard: Get out of here, you dirty rascals, this isn't the place for all your hullabaloo!
Sennosuke: But my Master...!
Alliance Guard: You're still here? Don't make me come after you! Disturbing the peace is a criminal offence!
Sennosuke: What should I do, Master...
Sennosuke: Who are you!?
Sennosuke: Ow... That hurts... Which of you blowhards...
???: You're a disciple of Kaito's?
Sennosuke: Who are you!
???: I see Kaito picked somebody just like himself...
Sennosuke: What are you bringing him up for! What's he to you?!
???: Me? I'm Kaito's brother in arms. Tell me, who killed him?
Sennosuke: Brother in arms... He never mentioned you...
Arrogant Hoodlum: Have you got any eyes in your head? That's the Boss of the Secret Society who's talking to you. Hurry up and answer him!
Secret Society Boss: Shut up, this doesn't concern you. Let him go and get out of my sight!
Secret Society Boss: So? Who killed Kaito?
Sennosuke: Why should I tell you anything? The Capybara Tribe drove me out, and the Alliance that Master told me to visit called me a troublemaker...
Sennosuke: There's nothing I can tell you that'll bring him back!
Secret Society Boss: Kaito told you to go to the Alliance? What a joke. He told you to look for them, and not for me.
Sennosuke: Master said... after he left the Society... he'd never go back again. Else nothing would ever change.
Secret Society Boss: Did Kaito live a happy life after he got out?
Secret Society Boss: Do you know why Kaito left the Society?
Sennosuke: I don't know... He said he'd tell me after the competition...
Secret Society Boss: He was quick to rush to battle at my command, but he could never accept my "deceitful methods", as he called them.
Secret Society Boss: Three years ago, I planned to extort the Cat Tribe through a kidnapping. Kaito quarrelled with me over it, and said he was leaving the Society.
Secret Society Boss: I told him to stay. Even if he left, he'd be marked out as a thug forevermore.
Sennosuke: He refused... to be part of your kidnapping... That does sound just like Master.
Secret Society Boss: If I'd known, I'd have forced him to stay.
Secret Society Boss: ...I'd rather have to force him than bury his bones.
Secret Society Boss: ...He's no longer a Society man, but he's still my brother in arms. And a brother in arms must have his vengeance. Tell me, who did this to Kaito?
Sennosuke: (Master wanted me to stay away from the Secret Society. But I can't get his revenge all by myself...!)
Sennosuke: (I'm sorry, Master...)
Sennosuke: Please, Yan-Bo must pay for this...!
Secret Society Boss: Heh.
Sennosuke: What are you laughing at...!

Secret Society Boss: Kaito never told a lie. The Capybaras have dared to make trouble, and it just so happens that they're standing in the way of my fortune now. I'll take this opportunity to destroy them.
Secret Society Boss: I'll use their deceit as an excuse, and...
Sennosuke: Boss! Master forbade me from joining the Society, but... I want to avenge him with my own hands!
Secret Society Boss: All right. I'll lend you a few men. Let me see what you can do.

Model.Text: Some days later...
(Today's the day of the meeting with Law and Maeok...)
Master Yan-Bo!
I heard about the accident during the Edensnatch, but I haven't been able find you since. Today I've finally caught up to you!
The Edensnatch...
Yes, Master. Are the rumors true?
We wanna know just exactly what happened that day before we can feel at ease joining your school.
I'm sorry. It's a little complicated...
We believe you, Master. But we want to hear it from your own mouth!
All I can say right now is that I did not cheat. The investigation isn't over yet, but in a few days the Capybara Chieftain will announce his findings...
Master Yan-Bo, can't you tell your future disciples anything at all? How can I call you Master otherwise?
W-wait a moment!
I told you so. Yan-Bo's not all you've cracked him up to be!
I misjudged you, Yan-Bo!
This is even more serious than I thought... If I go looking for Law and Maeok now I'll only drag them into it too...
I'll return to the Tribe first and ask them to carry them a message instead...
Get out of here, you dirty rascals, this isn't the place for all your hullabaloo!
But my Master...!
You're still here? Don't make me come after you! Disturbing the peace is a criminal offence!
What should I do, Master...
Who are you!?
Ow... That hurts... Which of you blowhards...
You're a disciple of Kaito's?
Who are you!
I see Kaito picked somebody just like himself...
What are you bringing him up for! What's he to you?!
Heh.
Me? I'm Kaito's brother in arms. Tell me, who killed him?
Brother in arms... He never mentioned you...
Have you got any eyes in your head? That's the Boss of the Secret Society who's talking to you. Hurry up and answer him!
Shut up, this doesn't concern you. Let him go and get out of my sight!
So? Who killed Kaito?
Why should I tell you anything? The Capybara Tribe drove me out, and the Alliance that Master told me to visit called me a troublemaker...
There's nothing I can tell you that'll bring him back!
Kaito told you to go to the Alliance? What a joke. He told you to look for them, and not for me.
Master said... after he left the Society... he'd never go back again. Else nothing would ever change.
Did Kaito live a happy life after he got out?
Do you know why Kaito left the Society?
I don't know... He said he'd tell me after the competition...
He was quick to rush to battle at my command, but he could never accept my "deceitful methods", as he called them.
Three years ago, I planned to extort the Cat Tribe through a kidnapping. Kaito quarrelled with me over it, and said he was leaving the Society.
I told him to stay. Even if he left, he'd be marked out as a thug forevermore.
He refused... to be part of your kidnapping... That does sound just like Master.
If I'd known, I'd have forced him to stay.
...I'd rather have to force him than bury his bones.
...He's no longer a Society man, but he's still my brother in arms. And a brother in arms must have his vengeance. Tell me, who did this to Kaito?
(Master wanted me to stay away from the Secret Society. But I can't get his revenge all by myself...!)
(I'm sorry, Master...)
Please, Yan-Bo must pay for this...!
Heh.
What are you laughing at...!
Kaito never told a lie. The Capybaras have dared to make trouble, and it just so happens that they're standing in the way of my fortune now. I'll take this opportunity to destroy them.
I'll use their deceit as an excuse, and...
Boss! Master forbade me from joining the Society, but... I want to avenge him with my own hands!
All right. I'll lend you a few men. Let me see what you can do.
